[[File:Dialekte Thüringen.PNG|thumb|300px|Dialects of Thuringian German: Central Thuringian in pale pink]] '''Central Thuringian''' ({{lang-de|Zentralthüringisch}}) is a [[Thuringian Dialect|Thuringian]] [[dialect]], that is spoken in the region of central Germany covered by the districts of [[Landkreis Gotha|Gotha]], [[Landkreis Sömmerda|Sömmerda]] and [[Ilm-Kreis]] as well as in the southern part of [[Unstrut-Hainich-Kreis|Unstrut-Hainich district]] and the city of [[Erfurt]]. A feature of the dialect are "falling [[diphthong]]s" (''fallende diphthonge'') (e.&nbsp;g. ''"Voater"'' instead of "Vater" (father)).
== Literature == * Wolfgang Lösch und andere: ''Kleines Thüringer Wörterbuch'', [[Reclam-Verlag]] Leipzig, 1995. {{ISBN|3-379-01521-0}}
