{{Infobox language |name=Hun-Saare |nativename=Saare, Duka |states=[[Nigeria]] |region=[[Kebbi State]], [[Niger State]] |speakers=73,000 |date=1985 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Kainji languages|Kainji]] |fam5=[[Northwest Kainji]] |dia1=Hun (Saare) |dia2=Saare |iso3=dud |glotto=huns1239 |glottorefname=Hun-Saare }}
'''Hun-Saare''' (Saare), or '''Duka''', is a [[Kainji language]] of [[Nigeria]]. The eastern and western dialects are known as ''Hun'' and ''Saare'' in the literature, but speakers use ''Saare'' for both.
