{{Infobox language |name=Jhankot Sign Language |states=[[Nepal]] |region=[[Dolpa District]] |speakers=?<!--no speaker numbers in the Ethnologue18--> |familycolor=Sign |family=[[village sign language|village sign]] |iso3=jhs |glotto=jhan1234 |glottorefname=Jhankot Sign Language }}
'''Jhankot Sign Language''' is a [[village sign language]] of the village of [[Jhankot]] in western [[Nepal]]. The Deaf make up 10% of the village, and Jhankot SL is widely known by the hearing community.
