* When unstressed, all vowels are somewhat raised {{IPA|[{{IPA link|i}}, {{IPA link|ɘ̝}}, {{IPA link|u}}, {{IPA link|ɪ}}, {{IPA link|ʊ}}, {{IPA link|ə}}]}}. The unstressed {{IPA|/ɐ/}} is the most strongly raised vowel. Utterance-final unstressed vowels are generally devoiced or even [[elision|elided]] when they occur after voiceless consonants, sometimes even after voiced consonants.{{sfnp|Sadowsky|Painequeo|Salamanca|Avelino|2013|pp=92–94}}
* {{IPA|/ɪ, ɘ, ʊ, ɐ/}} are often transcribed with {{angbr|{{IPA|i, ɨ, u, a}}}}.{{sfnp|Sadowsky|Painequeo|Salamanca|Avelino|2013|p=92}}
* {{IPA|/e, o/}} are somewhat centralized {{IPA|[{{IPA link|e|ë}}, {{IPA link|o|ö}}]}}.{{sfnp|Sadowsky|Painequeo|Salamanca|Avelino|2013|p=92}}
* {{IPA|/ɐ/}} is open-mid {{IPAblink|ɐ̝}}.{{sfnp|Sadowsky|Painequeo|Salamanca|Avelino|2013|p=92}}

{{IPA|/ɘ/}} is spelled {{angbr|ï}}, {{angbr|ü}}, or {{angbr|v}}, depending on the alphabet.

